                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" id="alamo_sng_1" hclass="sense" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/fort#fort_topg_1" title="fort definition"><span class="ndv">fort</span></a> (now in <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/san-antonio" title="San Antonio definition"><span class="ndv">San Antonio</span></a>, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/texas" title="Texas definition"><span class="ndv">Texas</span></a>) where an army of about 4 000 Mexican soldiers killed all 187 Texans defending it in 1836. <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/davy-crockett" title="Davy Crockett definition"><span class="ndv">Davy Crockett</span></a> and <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/james-bowie" title="James Bowie definition"><span class="ndv">James Bowie</span></a> died there. ‘Remember the Alamo!’ became a famous cry for Texas <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/independence_1" title="independence definition"><span class="ndv">independence</span></a> from Mexico. <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/john-wayne" title="John Wayne definition"><span class="ndv">John Wayne</span></a> directed and acted in a film about the battle, <span class="ebi">The Alamo</span> (1960).</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
